# 09_inspector_doc_walk — drive document-tier inspector widgets by abbrev.
#
# Post-s189 m1 the inspector's Button / Entry / CheckButton /
# ToggleButton / DropDown construction sites are all routed through
# curvz::widgets wrappers. Every set_name'd inspector widget is now
# scriptable by its abbrev.
#
# This script exercises three widgets that don't depend on object
# selection — they live in Document scope (Dimensions / Grid / Margins)
# and are addressable from launch with no setup. A future script can
# walk Object-scope widgets once it's framed around a selection-state
# precondition.
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.
#
# With pacing (s187 m4) cranked to 200-300ms this script becomes a
# tour of the inspector driving its own document settings — the kind
# of demonstration the teaching-medium frame (BOOK s188 m3) is for.

# ── Units dropdown ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Dimensions section's Units dropdown carries px / in / mm / pt.
# Pick each by visible text, assert the selection landed.

ins_can_un pick "px"
assert ins_can_un text == "px"

ins_can_un pick "in"
assert ins_can_un text == "in"

ins_can_un pick "mm"
assert ins_can_un text == "mm"

ins_can_un pick "pt"
assert ins_can_un text == "pt"

# Return to pixels — a reasonable launch state.
ins_can_un pick "px"
assert ins_can_un text == "px"

# ── Grid enable ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CheckButton at the top of the Grid section. Clicking toggles. The
# `set` verb forces a known state regardless of where we landed.

ins_grd_en set true
assert ins_grd_en active == true

ins_grd_en set false
assert ins_grd_en active == false

# ── Margins enable ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Same shape — CheckButton at the top of the Margins section.

ins_mrg_en set true
assert ins_mrg_en active == true

ins_mrg_en set false
assert ins_mrg_en active == false
